In this example, we will use the `fetch` API to send a GET request to a server and retrieve data.

### Using the Fetch API

The Fetch API provides a simple way to fetch resources asynchronously across the network.

```javascript
// Example usage
async function fetchData(url) {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(url);
    const data = await response.json();
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching data:', error);
  }
}

// Example usage
fetchData('https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts')
  .then(data => console.log(data))
  .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
```

